.TH "omap2_set_gpio_debounce" 9 "omap2_set_gpio_debounce" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
omap2_set_gpio_debounce \- low level gpio debounce time
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" omap2_set_gpio_debounce
.BI "(struct gpio_bank *bank "  ","
.BI "unsigned offset "  ","
.BI "unsigned debounce "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bank" 12
the gpio bank we're acting upon
.IP "offset" 12
the gpio number on this \fIbank\fP
.IP "debounce" 12
debounce time to use
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
OMAP's debounce time is in 31us steps
<debounce time> = (GPIO_DEBOUNCINGTIME[7:0].DEBOUNCETIME + 1) x 31
so we need to convert and round up to the closest unit.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, negative error otherwise.
